@startuml sequence_diagram

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor black
    ActorBorderColor black
    LifeLineBorderColor black
    ParticipantBorderColor black
    ParticipantBackgroundColor white
}

participant ":Producer" as P
participant "Named Pipe\n/ FIFO" as Pipe
participant ":Consumer" as C

== Startup ==

P -> Pipe : create pipe\n(server side)
P -> P    : waiting for consumer...

C -> Pipe : connect\n(retry loop)
Pipe --> P : consumer connected
Pipe --> C : connected to producer

== Event Loop ==

loop every 500 ms
    P -> P       : generateEvent()\n{ component, severity, message }
    P -> P       : serialize() → JSON string
    P -> Pipe    : write(json)
    Pipe -> C    : read(json)
    C -> C       : deserialize() → Event

    alt severity < WARNING
        C -> C   : discard event
    else severity >= WARNING
        C -> C   : update statistics\n(warning/error count)
        C -> C   : print event log
    end
end

== Statistics (every 5 s) ==

C -> C : printStatistics()\nWARNINGs / ERRORs\nper component

== Shutdown: Consumer exits ==

C ->x Pipe : close connection

P -> P     : WriteFile → BROKEN_PIPE\nreconnect()\nwaiting for new consumer...

...new consumer can connect again...

== Shutdown: Producer exits ==

P ->x Pipe : close / destroy pipe

Pipe -> C  : read() → EOF / BROKEN_PIPE
C -> C     : "Producer has disconnected.\nShutting down."

@enduml
